Cape Town â€” EXHIBITION space is almost sold out eight months before the 2018 edition of AfricaCom. According to organisers, over 85 percent of the exhibition hall is now booked. Among the over 250 early birds are leading brands from across the African technology and media sector including as Liquid Telecom, PCCW Global, Orange and NEC. James Bull, Business Development Director: Telecoms & Media: Knowledge and Networking at Informa, the organisers confirmed the bookings. He said additional space had been added due to huge demand. "The 2018 floor plan has been redesigned with additional stands added due to high demand," Bull said. AfricaCom will be held from November 13-15 in Cape Town, South Africa. It is the biggest industry exhibition in the continent.